$interpreted: : Legend has it that on this world there exist three others just like you. Perhaps you'd like to weave for us this strange tale...?
: Long, long ago, on the night of the year when the moon beams its brightest, an exquisite, luxurious fruit is produced: the beloved Bunny Blooms.

: Legend claims they are gifts from the full moon. It is also said that an official from the Security Council went on a relentless investigation in search of them. But in the end, his precious Bunny Blooms were stolen right from under him.
Federal Officer: ...This has all been robbed clean? This is already the sixth cultivation center that's been plundered...
Security Minister: Listen up. This is the first case of Bunny Blooms gone missing ever since they went extinct in the wild.
Federal Officer: And? You think I've got nothing to do? Don't come to me for such small matters.
Security Minister: What!? You must know that the Bunny Blooms are valued by the nobles.
Security Minister: Ever since they became extinct, there was a mad clamor to get their hands on them. That's why these cultivation centers were developed.
Security Minister: The situation as it is...would best be put as a matter of national security!
Federal Officer: Giving power to those idiots should be considered a matter of national security!
Federal Officer: ...Who is it!?
Federal Officer: Oh, it's you, you useless piece of junk. I said it before and I'll say it again. I don't need an assistant!
Assistant: Please, you are mistaken. The General ordered me to watch over you.
Federal Officer: *tsk*...asking me for help and then sending someone to watch my every move. Who does he think I am?

Assistant: Well, let's see. A Chief Federal Officer whose record shows you've broken into resident's houses without the requisite authority fifty-six times, destroyed a total of ten investigation sites, violated traffic laws a total of twenty-five times~
Federal Officer: Don't think I won't take you apart, you useless piece of shart.
Assistant: Ah, yes. The General wanted me to give you something to show that he trusts you'll do well. His own, handmade lunchbox~
Assistant: An analysis of it reveals that its function is decreasing rapidly. You must eat it quickly to absorb the maximum amount of nutrients.
Federal Officer: Get out of here!! Take it! Take that disgusting thing out of here and go!
Assistant: (Truly worthy of the code name "The Final Option"...what a detective.)
Federal Officer: Was that the sound of an explosion?
Purple-Cloak: *snickers*...these Bunny Blooms, by the night of the full moon, they'll all belong to us~
Purple-Cloak: Ah, the reinforcements have arrived.
Federal Officer: Put down the Bunny Blooms. For the time being, I'll only beat you half to death.
Assistant: Sir, you have not yet interrogated the suspect.
Federal Officer: Quit the yapping already! I'm here to uphold National Security, not to have a little chat!
Purple-Cloak: Oh, no~ What a scary little speech that was. Are you going to behave yourself like a good little boy?
Assistant: Relax. I will arrest him at the appropriate time.
Purple-Cloak: What a great idea. But are you sure you want to have at me right here?
Federal Officer: What did you just say?
Purple-Cloak: Now that all the Bunny Blooms have been stolen from the cultivation centers, what sort of rash thing do you think those nobles are willing to do just to get one?
Federal Officer: What are you planning? To bribe them?
Purple-Cloak: Bribery...too boring. I'm thinking...well, why don't you come and get me?
Federal Officer: Damn...he's gone.
Federal Officer: He left a map...looks like we've underestimated him.
Federal Officer: *chuckles*...so you want to play? Ohhhhh, I'll play alright!
Assistant: Sir, please note that the chemicals in your body that associated with anger are active to an excessive degree.
Federal Officer: Oh, shut your stinky mouth, ya piece of trash!!!
